CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 1, 1956, pg. B14, reads: "Deltas - Mu Chapter of Delta Sigma Theta Sorority held a Victory Ball at Hotel Fort Pitt as part of the 'Delta Weekend' festivities.  Entertaining their guests are, left to right, Edith Bradford, Theta Pyramid; Justine Robinson, vice president of Mu; Gloria Sterling, social chairman of Mu; Ella M. Mouitrie, Alpha Gamma, Morgan State; Irma Y. Cooke, Kappa Sigma, Jersey City, N. J., and Lillie Worthy, Theta Chapter. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Delta Sigma Theta sorority, Mu chapter members Edith Bradford, Justine Robinson, Gloria Sterling, Ella M. Mouitrie, Irma Y. Cooke, and Lillie Worthy posed in front of Rookwood mural in Norse Room, Fort Pitt Hotel
